# DEFENSIVE CYBERSPACE OPERATIONS and Objectives of Defensive Cyberspace Operations

## Cyberspace Actions include: 

	- Cyberspace Attack
	- Cyberspace Defense
	- Cyberspace Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance
	- Operational Preparation and Environment (OPE)

## Layers of Cyberspace:

	- Cyber Persona Layer
	- Physical Layer
	- Logical Layer

## Objectives of DCO: Are Unique to a Commander's Mission. 

	- Deter, Deny, and/or Defeat Adversary OCO
	- Gain Time
	- Defend Critical Assets
	- Control key terrain in Cyberspace (KT-C)

## Intelligence Support for DCO:

	- Organically Assigned Intelligence
	- J2.  G2, A2, and etc. 
	- Data intel form current Mission and leveraged

## Phases of DCO:

	- Screen 
	- Contain containment decisions
	- Clear
	- Secure

## Operational Preparation of the Environment (OPE):
	
-  Leadership Support Element:
	- Team Lead
		- Cyber Operations Planner
		- Operations 
		- NCOIC

-  Mission Element (ME): 
	- Mission Element Team Lead
		- Crew lead
		- Host Analyst
		- Network Analyst
		- and/or 

-  Operations Support: 
	- Host Analyst
	- Analytic Support Officer
	- Data Engineer
	- Network Technician
	- Network Analyst. 

-  Intelligence Support: 
	- All-Source Analyst M/S
	- All-Source Analyst S
	- All-Source Analyst B. 

-  CPT Work Roles: (CTM) 7-0.1 Joint Cyberspace Training and Certification Standards (JCT&CS).
-  CPT Team Work Roles: (CTM) 7-0.2 Cyber Mission Force.

## What Triggers the CPT Operations Process: 

	- Threat Intelligence
	- Campaign Plan
	- MCA Detection

## Planning the Mission: 

	- Phase 1 - Objectives Effects and Guidance
	- Phase 2 - Terrain Identification and Prioritization
	- Phase 3 - Capability Analysis and Force Allocation
	- Phase 4 - Orders Production and Dissemination
	- Phase 5 - Tactical Planning and Mission Execution
	- Phase 6 - Assessment and Analyzes of the MOP's



